 In his "Gun Control Is Constitutional" (Counterpoint, op-ed page, Dec. 12), the American Enterprise Institute's Robert A.
 Goldwin's principal concern, it seems, is to deny that the right to keep and bear arms precludes the power to regulate gun ownership and use.
 Thus he says that "In this version, `bearing arms' must mean `to render military service,' or why else would there have to be an exemption for religious reasons?
